<!-- 
This handlebar file will be rendered when the following route is hit: GET http://localhost:3000/
 
This page will respond with a valid HTML document. The title of the document should be "Marvel Universe Character Search". You should have the title set as the <title> element of the HTML document and as an h1 in your document.

Your page should reference a CSS file, /public/main.css; this file should have at least 10 rulesets you must use at least 5 of them on this page. 

You should have a main element, and inside of the main element have a p element with a brief (2-3 sentence description) of what your website does.

Also inside the main element, you will have a form; this form will POST to /searchmarveluniverse. This form will have an input and a label; You will give the input a name AND id attribute of "searchByCharactersName".  The label should properly reference the same id as the input. You should also have an input with a type of submit that submits the form (DO not use a button, you MUST use an input with type="submit"). 
 -->
    
    <main class="home-container">
        <h1 class="page-title">Marvel Character Search</h1>
        
        <p class="description">
            Search through the vast Marvel Universe to find information about your favorite characters. 
            Discover their comic appearances, descriptions, and images. 
        </p>
        <p class="description"> Start by entering a character name below.</p>
        
        <form action="/searchmarveluniverse" method="POST" class="search-form">
            <label for="searchByCharactersName" class="form-label">Character Name:</label>
            <input 
                type="text" 
                id="searchByCharactersName" 
                name="searchByCharactersName" 
                class="search-input"
                required
            >
            <input type="submit" value="Search" class="submit-btn">
        </form>
    </main>

